theorem P2_implies_closure_interior_closure_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 (A : Set X) →
      closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
  intro hP2
  -- From `P2` we have `closure (interior A) = closure A`.
  have hEq : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = closure A :=
    Topology.P2_implies_closure_interior_eq_closure (A := A) hP2
  -- Prove mutual inclusion.
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`
    have hSub : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono hSub
  · -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
    -- It suffices to show `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
    have hIntIncl :
        interior (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    have hClosIncl :
        closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      closure_mono hIntIncl
    simpa [hEq] using hClosIncl

theorem interior_subset_interior_closure_of_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (A : Set X) → interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  intro hP3
  -- Since `A ⊆ interior (closure A)` (by `P3`), applying `interior`
  -- monotonicity yields the desired inclusion.
  exact interior_mono hP3

theorem P2_and_open_closure_interior_implies_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 (A : Set X) →
      IsOpen (closure (interior (A : Set X))) →
      Topology.P3 (A : Set X) := by
  intro hP2 hOpen
  -- `P2` yields the equality of the two closures.
  have hEq : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = closure A :=
    Topology.P2_implies_closure_interior_eq_closure (A := A) hP2
  -- Combine openness with the equality to obtain `P3`.
  exact
    Topology.open_closure_interior_eq_closure_implies_P3
      (A := A) hOpen hEq
